Switch Statement
-----------------
        - It is used to choose an option among the given set of options
        - It is mainly used for menu driven applications

  syntax
  ------
        switch (expression)
            {
            case opt-1: statement;
                        break;
            case opt-2: statement;
                        break;
            case opt-3: statement;
                        break;
            case opt-n: statement;
                        break;
               default: statement;
             }
Point on switch statement
-------------------------
        - If expression is not matching with anyone of the options then it will execute
            the statement present in default
        - Default is optional
        - Default can be anywhere in between the options
        - Break is used to come out of switch
        - If break is not used then it will execute the statement present in other
          options until break
        - Expression should be of type int (byte/ short/ char)
        - From Java 7 version, expression can be of type String

        Example:
            String fruit= "apple";
            switch (fruit)
            {
            case "apple" : SOP("Apple");
                            break;
            case "mango" : SOP("Mango");
                            break;
            };

1. WAP to accept two numbers and display the following options/menu
        1.Add
        2.Subtract
        3.Multiply
        4.Divide
        Display result based on the user choice
        Example:
                n1=10, n2=5, ch=1 result =15
                n1=10, n2=5, ch=3 result =50
                n1=10, n2=5, ch=8 result =Invalided Choice

